# Gateway Rules

Local OpenAI-compatible HTTP server on **`127.0.0.1` only** (default port 4001).
Public reachability is via tunnel / BYO URL — see `tunnel.mdc`.

## Key model (upstream ×2 + gateway)

| Key                       | Config field           | Who sees it                          |
| ------------------------- | ---------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Moonshot / Kimi API key   | `moonshotKeyEncrypted` | App only → Authorization to Moonshot |
| DeepSeek API key          | `deepseekKeyEncrypted` | App only → Authorization to DeepSeek |
| Thaura AI API key         | `thauraKeyEncrypted`   | App only → Authorization to Thaura   |
| Gateway key (`sk-{alnum}`) | `gatewayKey`           | Cursor as “OpenAI API Key”           |

Never log or return upstream provider keys. Wrong gateway key → OpenAI-shaped 401.
Routing picks which upstream key to use from the **model map** (alias → provider).

### Upstream base URLs (code SoT)

Hardcoded defaults + optional env overrides live in
`internal/config/urls.go` (`UpstreamBaseURL`, `ChatCompletionsURL`).

| Provider | Default base                 |
| -------- | ---------------------------- |
| moonshot | `https://api.moonshot.ai/v1` |
| deepseek | `https://api.deepseek.com`   |
| thaura   | `https://backend.thaura.ai/v1` |

Use those helpers so Moonshot’s `/v1` and DeepSeek’s host root never produce
`/v1/v1/...`. Do not scatter raw URL string literals in the gateway proxy.

## Endpoints (MVP)

| Endpoint                    | Purpose                                              |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| `GET /health`               | Status, metrics, URLs, which provider keys present   |
| `GET\|POST /v1/models`      | Advertise aliases + real ids (+ provider)            |
| `POST /v1/chat/completions` | Main path                                            |
| `POST /v1/responses`        | Same handler after Responses→Chat adapt              |
| Other `/v1/*`               | Proxy when cheap (embeddings/files) — provider-aware |

## Model map (alias → provider → real id)

Switching providers/models for the user is **choosing the Cursor alias** (or a
listed real id). One table drives sanitize policy, upstream base URL, API key,
and pricing row.

### Primary Cursor aliases (Agent-first)

| Cursor alias     | Provider | Real model          | Typical use         |
| ---------------- | -------- | ------------------- | ------------------- |
| `gpt-5-high`     | moonshot | `kimi-k3`           | Planning / flagship |
| `gpt-5-codex`    | moonshot | `kimi-k2.6`         | Image-capable; thinking off by default |
| `gpt-4o`         | deepseek | `deepseek-v4-pro`   | Harder execution    |
| `gpt-4o-mini`    | deepseek | `deepseek-v4-flash` | Cheap execution     |
| `gpt-5-nano`     | thaura   | `thaura`            | Ethical AI; optional provider |

Set the alias manually in Cursor Settings → Models. The gateway maps it and
picks the right base URL + API key. No auto-application to Cursor's state.vscdb
— operators configure Cursor by hand (see `cursor-settings.mdc`).

## Sanitizer order (preserve)

1. Map Cursor alias → **{provider, real model}** (table above)
2. Apply **provider- and model-aware** thinking / sampling policy
   (`kimi.mdc` or `deepseek.mdc`)
3. Map `max_completion_tokens` → `max_tokens`; clamp per model context
4. Strip incompatible OpenAI/Cursor sampling fields
5. Adapt Responses `input`/`instructions` → `messages`
6. Repair tool_call ids / pairing; sanitize tool names + JSON Schema
7. Seed empty probe message when tools present and messages empty
8. Message role fixes (`developer`→`system`); reasoning placeholder for tool-call assistants when required

Then proxy to the resolved provider base URL with that provider’s key. Stream
what Cursor asked for (passthrough SSE or synthesize). Retry once on upstream
400s mentioning `tool_call_id` (when that provider returns them).

Behavioral checklist (Moonshot-oriented reference):
`examples/use-kimi-on-cursor/src-tauri/tests/`. DeepSeek: OpenAI shapes in
`examples/openai-openapi/` + `deepseek.mdc`.

### `Cursor Agent tool schema rejected`

| Symptom                                   | Cause                                                    | Fix                                              |
| ----------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| Upstream 400 on tools / empty Agent turns | MCP names, deep schemas, Responses shape, empty messages | Run full sanitizer order; seed probe; repair ids |

### `Wrong upstream after alias switch`

| Symptom                                                       | Cause                                                | Fix                                                            |
| ------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Request hits Moonshot while alias is DeepSeek (or vice versa) | Alias map missing provider field; hardcoded base URL | Resolve provider from map every request; select base URL + key |

### Go sanitizer library (`internal/gateway`)

Code SoT for alias resolve + request sanitize (T04+): `ResolveModel`,
`SanitizeRequest` → `SanitizeResult` with `Provider`, `Model`, and sanitized
`Body`. Unknown Cursor alias → error (HTTP layer maps to 400). **Strip order:**
apply provider thinking policy **before** stripping `reasoning_effort` — K3 must
keep `reasoning_effort: "max"`; do not copy reference K2 “strip effort then
inject thinking” blindly. K3: no `reasoning_content` placeholder injection.

### `Unknown variant image_url / Upstream 400 on vision content`

| Symptom                                                                                                                        | Cause                                                                                                                                                            | Fix                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        |
| ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Upstream returns 400 with `unknown variant image_url` or similar; occurs when Agent chat history includes screenshots / images | Cursor resends image content (`image_url`, `input_image`, `image_file`) in Agent message history; non-vision models (DeepSeek, some Moonshot) reject image parts | Strip `image_url`, `input_image`, and `image_file` content parts in both chat-completion messages (`sanitizeMessageContent`) and Responses-shaped input (`convertInputItems`, `normalizeContentParts`). Replace with `[image omitted]` text placeholder. Applies to both `/v1/chat/completions` and `/v1/responses` paths. |

